-- U.K.'s Benchmark FTSE 100 Advances for Seventh Day; BP Shares Lead Gains
-- Andrew Rummer
-- 2010-06-17T07:09:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-17/u-k-s-benchmark-ftse-100-advances-for-seventh-day-bp-shares-lead-gains.html

          
          
             U.K. stocks rose for a seventh day,
the longest stretch of gains in almost 11 months, as BP Plc
surged. The FTSE 100 Index advanced 0.3 percent to 5,251.36 at
8:07 a.m. in London.  
          
          


  


        